# Trivy escapes for the e2e-smoke image scan (ci.yml points here, so the file
# must exist even when empty — tests/test_ci_artifacts.py asserts that).
#
# Any entry must carry a justification + an explicit removal condition,
# and (when the advisory also appears in the PyPI feed) be mirrored as a
# pip-audit --ignore-vuln escape in ci.yml plus an entry in the
# TestVulnEscapesCannotRot.ESCAPED map so it cannot rot.
#
# Currently ZERO escapes. (The former CVE-2026-42504 entry excused the Go
# stdlib inside the upstream caddy binary — the caddy image was retired with
# the move to Cloudflare Tunnel, so the escape went with it.)
